title: Can Food Be Art? Denmark Is Finding Out.
description: High-level chefs in the country could become eligible for arts funding under a new initiative. Not all in the art and culinary worlds are raising a glass to the idea, though.

title: Former U.S. ambassador to Denmark on anger over Greenland, Trump's comments about NATO soldiers
description: Rufus Gifford, a former U.S. ambassador to Denmark, is reacting to President Trump's claims about NATO soldiers fighting during the Afghanistan War, and says the Danish people are grieving after Mr. Trump's push to acquire Greenland. CBS News' Ramy Inocencio reports.

title: Severe cold persists as forecasters track another potential East Coast storm
description: Maps show where the next blast of Arctic air and a potential winter storm are expected to travel this weekend, according to the latest forecast models.

title: Frigid Temps Grip US as East Coast Braces for Another Storm
description: A deadly winter freeze is gripping the United States with days of icy roads, heavy snow and freezing temperatures. In Arkansas, a courthouse collapsed under the weight of heavy snow. It comes as another arctic blast and a bomb cyclone is on the way this weekend. NBC’s Stephanie Gosk reports and TODAY’s Al Roker tracks the forecast.

title: WATCH:  US Coast Guard deploys ice breaking ships in New York City amid Arctic blast
description: A fresh blast of life-threatening cold is impacting over 150 million – including those in New York City, which is in the grip of its deepest freeze in eight years.
